ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.55                 Enzyme
NAME        (S)-beta-bisabolene synthase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     (2E,6E)-farnesyl-diphosphate diphosphate-lyase [(S)-beta-bisabolene-forming]
REACTION    (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate = (S)-beta-bisabolene + diphosphate [RN:R09623]
ALL_REAC    R09623
SUBSTRATE   (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C00448]
PRODUCT     (S)-beta-bisabolene [CPD:C19751];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     The synthesis of (S)-beta-macrocarpene from (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate proceeds in two steps. The first step is the cyclization to (S)-beta-bisabolene. The second step is the isomerization to (S)-beta-macrocarpene (cf. EC 5.5.1.17, (S)-beta-macrocarpene synthase). The enzyme requires Mg2+ or Mn2+ for activity.
HISTORY     EC 4.2.3.55 created 2011
